wikipedia_page.main: Anna Cheyne HRUA (9 April 1926–10 September 2002) was an artist and sculptor, born and educated in England but moved to Northern Ireland after her marriage to architect Donald Cheyne.

response: From the late 1960s and early 1970s Boyle became obsessed with the myths and songs of Sweeney, the cursed Celtic King, producing in excess of thirty paintings in a theme that enveloped her work for the remaining thirty years of her life.Pyle, (1990), p.24 Between 1983 and 1989 Boyle had five solo exhibitions and three major retrospectives. Boyle was inaugurated into the National Self Portrait Collection of Ireland in 1995, alongside twelve others including Joseph O'Connor, Sidney Smith, Anna Cheyne and George Russell.
